<paragraph blockId="7.[168,778,1212,2091]" pageId="7" pageNumber="330">
<emphasis inLineHeading="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="330" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[168,330,1486,1510]" pageId="7" pageNumber="330">Identification.</emphasis>
Our specimens were identified as 
<taxonomicName class="Agaricomycetes" family="Hymenochaetaceae" genus="Fomitiporia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Hymenochaetales" pageId="7" pageNumber="330" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="neotropica">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="330">F. neotropica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
based on the characters given by 
<bibRefCitation author="Campos-Santana M &amp; Robledo G &amp; Silveira RMB &amp; Decock C" pageId="7" pageNumber="330" pagination="601 - 615" refId="ref5044" refString="Campos-Santana M, Robledo G, Silveira RMB, Decock C (2014) Fomitiporia neotropica, a new species from South America evidenced by multilocus phylogenetic analyses. Mycological Progress 13 (3): 601 - 615. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / s 11557 - 013 - 0943 - 1" type="journal article" year="2014">Campos-Santana et al. (2014)</bibRefCitation>
: basidiome perennial, resupinate to effused-reflexed (
<figureCitation box="[360,448,1587,1611]" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="5.[168,231,1980,2000]" captionTargetBox="[168,1419,160,1956]" captionTargetId="figure-35@5.[168,1419,160,1956]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figure 3. Macroscopic structures (hymenophore, pileal region, pores of hymenophore, tubes and context). A. Fomitiporia langloisii. B. F. maxonii. C. F. murrillii. D. F. neotropica." pageId="7" pageNumber="330">Fig. 3D</figureCitation>
), hymenophoral surface with circular to ellipsoid pores, 5–9 per mm (
<figureCitation box="[622,708,1620,1644]" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="5.[168,231,1980,2000]" captionTargetBox="[168,1419,160,1956]" captionTargetId="figure-35@5.[168,1419,160,1956]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figure 3. Macroscopic structures (hymenophore, pileal region, pores of hymenophore, tubes and context). A. Fomitiporia langloisii. B. F. maxonii. C. F. murrillii. D. F. neotropica." pageId="7" pageNumber="330">Fig. 3D</figureCitation>
), context homogeneous, golden (
<figureCitation box="[492,584,1654,1678]" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="5.[168,231,1980,2000]" captionTargetBox="[168,1419,160,1956]" captionTargetId="figure-35@5.[168,1419,160,1956]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figure 3. Macroscopic structures (hymenophore, pileal region, pores of hymenophore, tubes and context). A. Fomitiporia langloisii. B. F. maxonii. C. F. murrillii. D. F. neotropica." pageId="7" pageNumber="330">Fig. 3D</figureCitation>
); hyphal system dimitic, with generative hyphae hyaline to slightly yellowish, thin-walled, septate (
<figureCitation box="[493,583,1721,1745]" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="6.[169,232,1980,2000]" captionTargetBox="[171,1412,187,1931]" captionTargetId="figure-13@6.[169,1419,184,1933]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figure 4. Microscopic structures (generative hyphae - left; skeletal hyphae - right; basidiospores). A. Fomitiporia apiahyna. B. F. calkinsii. C. F. conyana. D. F. impercepta. E. F. langloisii. F.F. maxonii. G. F.murrillii. H. F.neotropica." pageId="7" pageNumber="330">Fig. 4H</figureCitation>
); skeletal hyphae pale brown, thick-walled, nonseptate (
<figureCitation box="[584,670,1754,1779]" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="6.[169,232,1980,2000]" captionTargetBox="[171,1412,187,1931]" captionTargetId="figure-13@6.[169,1419,184,1933]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figure 4. Microscopic structures (generative hyphae - left; skeletal hyphae - right; basidiospores). A. Fomitiporia apiahyna. B. F. calkinsii. C. F. conyana. D. F. impercepta. E. F. langloisii. F.F. maxonii. G. F.murrillii. H. F.neotropica." pageId="7" pageNumber="330">Fig. 4H</figureCitation>
); basidiospores dextrinoid, subglobose to obvoid, hyaline, thickwalled, 5–7 × 4.5–6 μm (
<figureCitation box="[441,526,1821,1846]" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="6.[169,232,1980,2000]" captionTargetBox="[171,1412,187,1931]" captionTargetId="figure-13@6.[169,1419,184,1933]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figure 4. Microscopic structures (generative hyphae - left; skeletal hyphae - right; basidiospores). A. Fomitiporia apiahyna. B. F. calkinsii. C. F. conyana. D. F. impercepta. E. F. langloisii. F.F. maxonii. G. F.murrillii. H. F.neotropica." pageId="7" pageNumber="330">Fig. 4H</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="330" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="7.[168,778,1212,2091]" pageId="7" pageNumber="330">
<emphasis inLineHeading="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="330" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[168,280,1860,1884]" pageId="7" pageNumber="330">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[288,544,1861,1884]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Hymenochaetaceae" genus="Fomitiporia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Hymenochaetales" pageId="7" pageNumber="330" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="neotropica">
<emphasis box="[288,544,1861,1884]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="330">Fomitiporia neotropica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName class="Agaricomycetes" family="Hymenochaetaceae" genus="Fomitiporia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Hymenochaetales" pageId="7" pageNumber="330" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="maxonii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="330">F. maxonii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
, differing mainly by the number of tube layers: in 
<taxonomicName box="[168,316,1928,1951]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Hymenochaetaceae" genus="Fomitiporia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Hymenochaetales" pageId="7" pageNumber="330" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="neotropica">
<emphasis box="[168,316,1928,1951]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="330">F. neotropica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
there are two layers, while in 
<taxonomicName box="[660,778,1928,1951]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Hymenochaetaceae" genus="Fomitiporia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Hymenochaetales" pageId="7" pageNumber="330" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="maxonii">
<emphasis box="[660,778,1928,1951]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="330">F. maxonii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
there are up to four (
<bibRefCitation author="Decock C &amp; Figueroa SH &amp; Robledo G &amp; Castillo G" box="[403,617,1961,1985]" pageId="7" pageNumber="330" pagination="733 - 752" refId="ref5299" refString="Decock C, Figueroa SH, Robledo G, Castillo G (2007) Fomitiporia punctata (Basidiomycota, Hymenochaetales) and its presumed taxonomic synonyms in America: taxonomy and phylogeny of some species from tropical / subtropical areas. Mycologia 99 (5): 733 - 752. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 15572536.2007.11832537" type="journal article" year="2007">Decock et al. 2007</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Campos-Santana M &amp; Robledo G &amp; Silveira RMB &amp; Decock C" pageId="7" pageNumber="330" pagination="601 - 615" refId="ref5044" refString="Campos-Santana M, Robledo G, Silveira RMB, Decock C (2014) Fomitiporia neotropica, a new species from South America evidenced by multilocus phylogenetic analyses. Mycological Progress 13 (3): 601 - 615. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / s 11557 - 013 - 0943 - 1" type="journal article" year="2014">Campos-Santana et al. 2014</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="330" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="7.[168,778,1212,2091]" pageId="7" pageNumber="330">
<emphasis box="[168,778,2033,2057]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="330" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[168,317,2033,2057]" pageId="7" pageNumber="330">Distribution.</emphasis>
In 
<collectingCountry box="[364,433,2033,2057]" name="Brazil" pageId="7" pageNumber="330">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[450,601,2034,2057]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Hymenochaetaceae" genus="Fomitiporia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Hymenochaetales" pageId="7" pageNumber="330" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="neotropica">
<emphasis box="[450,601,2034,2057]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="330">F. neotropica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is only known
</emphasis>
from southern 
<collectingCountry box="[330,397,2067,2091]" name="Brazil" pageId="7" pageNumber="330">Brazil</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Campos-Santana M &amp; Robledo G &amp; Silveira RMB &amp; Decock C" box="[412,720,2067,2091]" pageId="7" pageNumber="330" pagination="601 - 615" refId="ref5044" refString="Campos-Santana M, Robledo G, Silveira RMB, Decock C (2014) Fomitiporia neotropica, a new species from South America evidenced by multilocus phylogenetic analyses. Mycological Progress 13 (3): 601 - 615. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / s 11557 - 013 - 0943 - 1" type="journal article" year="2014">Campos-Santana et al. 2014</bibRefCitation>
), and
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[810,1420,160,218]" pageId="7" pageNumber="330">our record is the first time this species has been found in the Amazonian region.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
